The '''Agrilat Region''', also known as the '''Agrilat Swamp''', the '''Crystal Swamps''' or simply '''Agrilat''', was a region located on the [[Corellia's northern continent|northern continent]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. Situated between the northern sea and the [[Orik's Spine/Legends|Orik's Spine]] mountain range, the region was largely composed of [[Swamp/Legends|swamps]] filled with crystalline plants like [[razor grass]]. It was a hot spot for illegal [[Swoop racing/Legends|swoop races]], such as the [[Agrilat Swamp Circuit]]. The [[Dragonbane circuit]] was also located in this region.<ref name="SoF" />

The swamps were the site of a famous race between [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]], a cult hero of the professional racing circuit, and another youth named [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], from the private circuit. Tired of constantly being compared to Solo, Dengar challenged his rival to a winner-takes-all race through the dangerous swamps. During the race, Solo's [[Stabilizer/Legends|stabilizer fin]] became entangled with Dengar's, causing Dengar to lose control and crash.<ref name="Galaxy Guide 3">''[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back]]''</ref>

At some point before [[29 BBY/Legends|29 BBY]], Agrilat was also known for producing mouth-loosening [[Agrilat drugs|drugs]].<ref name="Rogue Planet">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> wild creatures from the Agrilat Swamp wandered into more civilized areas of Corellia and threatened local farmers. [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Moss Shelby]] of [[Corellian Security Force|CorSec]]'s [[Regiment Twelve]] therefore hired a group of [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]] to hunt the animals.<ref name="SWG:LCotM" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Agrilat_concept_art.jpg|thumb|right|280px|Concept art of the Agrilat Swamp for [[Star Wars Galaxies|''Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided'']].]]
There is some discrepancy as to whether Agrilat is a region on Corellia or a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] unto its own. The PC game [[Star Wars: Rebellion (video game)|''Star Wars: Rebellion'']] and ''[[Star Wars: Rebellion: Prima's Official Strategy Guide]]'' place Agrilat as a planet in the [[Moddell sector/Legends|Moddell sector]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]], ''[[Star Wars: The Visual Dictionary]]'' indicates it is a planet in the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]], [[Star Wars Gamer 6|''Star Wars Gamer'' 6]] indicates that it is a city on Corellia, ''[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back]]'' simply states it is a swamp located in the [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]], and ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'' indicates Agrilat is a swamp on Corellia itself. ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'' has one reference to the crystal swamps comparing them to other natural beauties found on Corellia.

